What we did internally is passing an NIL task id for the main thread (because in node manager you can get the real task id from `worker.GetAssignedTaskId()`), and random task ids for other threads. In this way, you don't need access to `WorkerContext` in `RayletClientImpl`. 

If you still prefer passing the real task id for main thread from worker, you can pass the `runtime` as a parameter to the constructor of `RayletClientImpl` (in `RayNativeRuntime.start`), then you can access `workerContext` by `runtime.getWorkerContext()`.

