Deadlocks in tests are, in my opinion, a pain in the neck:
 * they push the test execution on CI up to the timeout (which can often be 10 to 30 minutes), even for quick unit tests;
 * they consume CI resources during that time (which is not irrelevant given that free CI options generally limit the amount of computing resources that can be used);
 * they prevent the generation of a test report - which complicates the "fix the test" workflow;

I believe adding a simple, small line is well worth ensuring that this test will never be the cause of such issues. (It really makes the "test the regression" workflow easier, too!)

